Income Statement: The company will recognize a loss on the sale of the factory in the income statement, which is calculated as the difference between the book value of the factory ($100) and the selling price ($80). The loss will be $20. The company will save $8 on taxes (40% of $20). So the net impact on the income statement will be a reduction of $12 in net income.

Balance Sheet: The company will reduce the factory asset account on the balance sheet by $100. In addition, the company will recognize cash inflows of $80 from the sale. So the net impact on the balance sheet will be a decrease of $20 in assets.

Cash Flow Statement: Will reflect the inflow of $80 from the sale of the factory in the "Investing Activities" section. The impact on the cash flow statement will be an inflow of $80, which will increase the company's cash balance.